It was impossible to make any change in the de- curiae of senators, since probably the tribes were not all repre- sented in the senate, or, if all, only very unequally ; but Gnaeus Pompeius went back to an old ordinance for the choice of jurors for the decuriae of equites and tribuni aerarii according to tribes (tributim), which was enforced by the lex Sempronia but afterwards abrogatcd by Sulla and not revived by L.
